Variables in Java:
1. Local - declared and accessed ONLY inside method, constructor, block

	public void hello(String name) {
		name="Jack";
		System.out.println("Hello "+name);
	}

	CANNOT BE USED WITH ACCESS MODIFIERS AND CANNOT BE STATIC
	dataType name

2. Instance (global) - declared inside the class but outside of method, constructor or clock; accesible within a class

	private String name="John";

	instance variable CAN BE USED WITH access modifiers

3. Static/Class (global) - declared inside the class but outside method, constructor or block and they use STATIC keyword

	static String breed="Husky";
	static int paws=4;

	static/class variable CAN BE USED WITH access modifiers